Orin Larsen is a professional bareback rider from Inglis, Manitoba, Canada, who has made a name for himself in the rodeo world. With multiple National Finals Rodeo (NFR) qualifications and over $1.1 million in career earnings, Larsen has become a prominent figure in the sport.

Here you can follow Orin Larsen’s net worth, career earnings, professional career, achievements, relationship status, and more.

About Orin Larsen

Orin Larsen was born in Strathmore, Alberta, Canada, and raised in Inglis, Manitoba. He comes from a family with a strong rodeo background, which has played a significant role in shaping his career. 

Larsen currently resides in Gering, Nebraska, with his wife, Alexa, who works as an ICU nurse.

Early Career

Larsen began his rodeo journey by competing in college rodeo events. He attended the College of Southern Idaho and later Oklahoma Panhandle State University, where he won the 2013 College National Bareback Championship.

Professional Career

Orin Larsen began his professional rodeo career in 2010 when he joined the Professional Rodeo Cowboys Association (PRCA). Since then, he has qualified for the Wrangler National Finals Rodeo (NFR) nine times.

Larsen has had numerous major regular-season wins throughout his career. These include victories at the New Town Rodeo Days, Reno Rodeo, Utah Days of ’47 Rodeo, California Rodeo Salinas, Fallon County Fair & Rodeo, Calgary Stampede, and Ponoka Stampede.

In 2016, Larsen won his first Cheyenne Frontier Days (CFD) bareback riding championship. He also won the 2019 Canadian Championship, marking his first Canadian title.

Despite a thumb injury that sidelined him during a previous NFR, Larsen made a strong comeback, proving his resilience and dedication to the sport.

In 2023, he entered the Thomas & Mack as the No. 6 ranked bareback rider in the world, with $147,237 in total earnings.

Larsen’s career earnings have surpassed $1.5 million, reflecting his success and longevity in the sport. His professional career is characterized by his competitive nature, love for riding bareback horses, and his ability to bounce back from setbacks.

Orin Larsen’s Net Worth in 2023

As of 2023, Orin Larsen’s net worth is estimated to be $3 million.

Career Earnings

Orin Larsen has had a successful career in professional rodeo, with his earnings reflecting his accomplishments. Since his rookie year in 2011, Larsen has accumulated over $1.5 million in career earnings.

In 2019, Larsen finished second in the world standings with $296,404. He placed fourth in the Wrangler NFR average, earning $122,962.

In 2023, Larsen entered Thomas & Mack as the No. 6 ranked bareback rider in the world, with $147,237 in total earnings.

Throughout his career, Larsen has had numerous major regular-season wins that have contributed to his earnings. 

For instance, he earned $5,288 at the New Town Rodeo Days, $5,405 at the Reno Rodeo, $8,500 at the Utah Days of ’47 Rodeo, $11,078 at the California Rodeo Salinas, $6,054 at the Fallon County Fair & Rodeo, $5,875 at the Calgary Stampede, and $15,996 at the Ponoka Stampede.

Endorsements

Orin Larsen is endorsed by Durango Boot, a popular brand in the rodeo community.

Personal Details

Wife

Orin Larsen is happily married to his wife, Alexa. The couple tied the knot in 2017 and have been together for almost five years. 

Alexa is active on Instagram, where she often shares adorable pictures of the pair together and praises her husband through her posts and stories.

How Old is Orin Larsen?

He is 32 years old.

What is his nationality?

He is Canadian.

FAQs About Orin Larsen

What is Orin Larsen’s primary rodeo event?

Orin Larsen is a professional bareback rider.

How many times has he qualified for the NFR?

He has qualified for the Wrangler National Finals Rodeo multiple times.

Who is his wife?

Alexa, an ICU nurse.
